text: Krzysztof Lipiński (born July 14, 1984) is a Polish luger who competed from 1999 to 2006. He finished 17th in the men's doubles event at the 2006 Winter Olympics in Turin. Lipiński's best finish at the FIL World Luge Championships was 19th in the men's doubles event at Park City, Utah in 2005. ==References== * 2006 luge men's doubles results * FIL-Luge profile Category:1983 births Category:Living people Category:Lugers at the 2006 Winter Olympics Category:Polish male lugers Category:Olympic lugers of Poland Category:People from Kostrzyn Category:Sportspeople from Greater Poland Voivodeship
